Target file: src/beads_bridge.rs (verify exact path in repo root before starting)

Pre-flight check: Before running any automation script, open scripts/run-swarm.sh and confirm line 98 initializes `_prev_arg` before use. If it does not, add `_prev_arg=""` at the top of the relevant function or loop block. Confirm the script runs without error on a no-op invocation before proceeding.

Step 1 — Add the helper function. Insert the following into src/beads_bridge.rs at module scope (not inside an existing function):

pub fn default_actor() -> String {
    if let Ok(val) = std::env::var("BD_ACTOR") {
        if !val.trim().is_empty() {
            return val;
        }
    }
    if let Ok(output) = std::process::Command::new("git")
        .args(&["config", "user.name"])
        .output()
    {
        let name = String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stdout).trim().to_string();
        if !name.is_empty() {
            return name;
        }
    }
    hostname::get()
        .ok()
        .and_then(|h| h.into_string().ok())
        .unwrap_or_else(|| "unknown".to_string())
}

Step 2 — Replace inline reads. Search src/beads_bridge.rs for every occurrence of `std::env::var("BD_ACTOR")` and `env::var("BD_ACTOR")`. Replace each inline fallback chain with a call to `default_actor()`. Do not leave any duplicate fallback logic in place.

Step 3 — Check dependencies. If the `hostname` crate is not already in Cargo.toml, add it (e.g., `hostname = "0.3"`). Run `cargo build` and confirm zero errors before committing.

Step 4 — Verify. Run `cargo test` and confirm existing tests pass. If there are tests that mock BD_ACTOR via environment variables, confirm they still work correctly since `default_actor()` reads the same env var first.

Acceptance criteria: `default_actor()` is `pub`, lives in beads_bridge.rs, implements the three-step fallback (BD_ACTOR env -> git user.name -> hostname), and all former inline BD_ACTOR reads are replaced with calls to it."}

